      • launch

        default boolean launch()
                throws CouldNotPerformException,
                       InterruptedException
        Method starts the referred application.
        Returns:
        returns true if the application was successfully started in case the application was started with restrictions false will be returned.
        Throws:
        CouldNotPerformException - Is thrown in case any error occurs during the startup phase.
        InterruptedException - is thrown in case the thread was externally interrupted.
